Statement.md

Project Title: UPSC Preparation Chatbot
Course: Introduction to Problem Solving & Programming

1. Purpose or Goal of the Project

The goal of this project was to develop a simple chatbot that runs in the command line using Python. The chatbot is designed to assist users by providing basic information related to UPSC preparation, such as exam pattern, subjects, recommended books, and current affairs.

It interacts with the user in a conversational manner, responds to queries based on predefined keywords, and provides instant answers.

2. Requirements

The task was to design an interactive chatbot program that uses basic programming concepts such as:

Handling user input
Using dictionaries for storing responses
Implementing loops and conditional logic
Performing keyword matching
Structuring code into functions
3. System Design
Data Structure:
A dictionary is used to store predefined responses. Each key represents a keyword (such as "upsc", "prelims", "books"), and the value contains the corresponding response.
User Interaction:
The chatbot continuously takes user input and checks for matching keywords to generate appropriate responses.
4. Top-Down Design / Modularization

To ensure proper design, the program was structured into functions:

chatbot():
This is the main function and entry point of the program. It handles:
Displaying the welcome message
Managing the conversation loop
Processing user input
Matching keywords with responses
Handling special commands like “help” and “exit”

This modular approach keeps the logic organized and easy to maintain.

5. Algorithm Development
Program Flow:
Display a welcome message for the chatbot.
Prompt the user to enter a query.
Convert the input to lowercase for consistency.
Check if the user entered:
“exit” → terminate the program
“help” → display available topics
greetings like “hi”, “hello” → respond accordingly
Search for keywords in the user input.
If a match is found, display the corresponding response.
If no match is found, display an error message.
Repeat the process until the user exits.
6. Implementation
Language: Python 3
Input Handling: User input is converted to lowercase to ensure consistent matching of keywords regardless of case.
Logic Used: Dictionary lookup, loops, and conditional statements are used to control chatbot behavior.
7. Testing and Refinement

The chatbot was tested manually to ensure correct functionality:

User Input: Tested with different inputs including valid keywords, greetings, and random text.
Keyword Matching: Verified that correct responses are returned for matching inputs.
Help Command: Ensured all available topics are displayed correctly.
Exit Condition: Confirmed that typing “exit” terminates the chatbot.
Refinement: Improved responses and added user-friendly messages for better interaction.
8. Conclusion

This project successfully demonstrates the use of basic Python programming concepts to build an interactive chatbot. The chatbot is simple, user-friendly, and effectively provides useful information related to UPSC preparation.

9. Future Enhancements

Potential improvements include:

Expanding the knowledge base with more topics
Implementing Natural Language Processing (NLP) for better understanding
Adding voice-based interaction
Creating a graphical user interface (GUI)
Integrating real-time data sources for current affairs updates
